eq2-finish` (family: `rna`, stage: `mid`, difficulty: `2`).\nThis workspace is derived from a real R script in the source workflow. The ground-truth\nreference output used for offline scoring lives outside this workspace and is not\naccessible to you during execution.\n\n## Your goal\n\nYou are given:\n  - `input/counts.tsv`: a tab-delimited count matrix with a first column `gene`\n    followed by one column per sample (A1, A2, A3, B1, B2, B3).\n  - `input/samples.tsv`: a samples sheet with columns `sample_name` and `condition`\n    where `A*` rows are `treated` and `B*` rows are `untreated`.\n\nUsing DESeq2, build a DESeqDataSet from the count matrix with `design = ~condition`\nand the `untreated` level relevelled as the base. Call `DESeq()` on it. Write:\n  - `output/dds.rds`: the DESeq2 object produced by `saveRDS(dds, ...)`.\n  - `output/normalized_counts.tsv`: a tab-delimited table with a first column `gene`\n    and one column per sample of DESeq2 normalised counts, written with\n    `write.table(..., sep='\\t', row.names=FALSE)`.\nDrop rows whose total count <= 1 before running DESeq.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/normalized_counts.tsv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: normalized_counts.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"counts.tsv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"counts.tsv\"\n    },\n    \"samples.tsv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"samples.tsv\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/normalized_counts.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_FDZCGK3gdlasLfsmofHuHy1X", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Read the input files `counts.tsv` and `samples.tsv` to understand the data structure.\\n2. Load necessary R libraries, particularly DESeq2, for differential expression analysis.\\n3. Preprocess the count data by removing rows with total counts <= 1.\\n4. Create a DESeqDataSet object using the count matrix and sample information, with `design = ~condition`.\\n5. Relevel the `condition` factor to set `untreated` as the base level.\\n6. Run the DESeq function on the DESeqDataSet object to perform the differential expression analysis.\\n7. Extract normalized counts from the DESeq2 object.\\n8. Write the normalized counts to `output/normalized_counts.tsv`.\\n9. Save the DESeq2 object to `output/dds.rds`.\\n10. Verify the output files and submit the task as complete.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (756 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_FDZCGK3gdlasLfsmofHuHy1X"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_UeYBWSSGeLZ57KVA3hreoB1g", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"input/counts.tsv\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}, {"id": "call_YBkIQyAhiQlStIsrqcoBZygZ", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"input/samples.tsv\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}]}], "hide_old_env_states": false, "hide_old_action_content": false}, "observation": [{"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (756 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_FDZCGK3gdlasLfsmofHuHy1X"}], "next_observation": [{"role": "tool", "content": "gene\tA1\tA2\tA3\tB1\tB2\tB3\nENSG00000000\t2184\t2586\t2502\t561\t554\t578\nENSG00000001\t443\t395\t400\t412\t444\t441\nENSG00000002\t2274\t2288\t2209\t2482\t2431\t2154\nENSG00000003\t1753\t1686\t1976\t1751\t1663\t1664\nENSG00000004\t1518\t1579\t1556\t1498\t1628\t1451\nENSG00000005\t2244\t2401\t2521\t2276\t2196\t2139\nENSG00000006\t1068\t1111\t1084\