\n  - `input/samples.tsv`: a samples sheet with columns `sample_name` and `condition`\n    where `A*` rows are `treated` and `B*` rows are `untreated`.\n\nUsing DESeq2, build a DESeqDataSet from the count matrix with `design = ~condition`\nand the `untreated` level relevelled as the base. Call `DESeq()` on it. Write:\n  - `output/dds.rds`: the DESeq2 object produced by `saveRDS(dds, ...)`.\n  - `output/normalized_counts.tsv`: a tab-delimited table with a first column `gene`\n    and one column per sample of DESeq2 normalised counts, written with\n    `write.table(..., sep='\\t', row.names=FALSE)`.\nDrop rows whose total count <= 1 before running DESeq.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/normalized_counts.tsv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: normalized_counts.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"counts.tsv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"counts.tsv\"\n    },\n    \"samples.tsv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"samples.tsv\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/normalized_counts.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_FDZCGK3gdlasLfsmofHuHy1X", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Read the input files `counts.tsv` and `samples.tsv` to understand the data structure.\\n2. Load necessary R libraries, particularly DESeq2, for differential expression analysis.\\n3. Preprocess the count data by removing rows with total counts <= 1.\\n4. Create a DESeqDataSet object using the count matrix and sample information, with `design = ~condition`.\\n5. Relevel the `condition` factor to set `untreated` as the base level.\\n6. Run the DESeq function on the DESeqDataSet object to perform the differential expression analysis.\\n7. Extract normalized counts from the DESeq2 object.\\n8. Write the normalized counts to `output/normalized_counts.tsv`.\\n9. Save the DESeq2 object to `output/dds.rds`.\\n10. Verify the output files and submit the task as complete.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (756 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_FDZCGK3gdlasLfsmofHuHy1X"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_UeYBWSSGeLZ57KVA3hreoB1g", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"input/counts.tsv\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}, {"id": "call_YBkIQyAhiQlStIsrqcoBZygZ", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"input/samples.tsv\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}]}], "hide_old_env_states": false, "hide_old_action_content": false}, "next_agent_state": {"tools": [{"type": "function", "info": {"name": "run_shell", "description": "Run a shell command in the task work_dir (bash -lc).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"command": {"description": "Shell command string passed to `bash -lc`.", "title": "Command", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["command"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "read_text_file", "description": "Read a UTF-8 text file relative to work_dir.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"relative_path": {"description": "Path under the workspace (not absolute).", "title": "Relative Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["relative_path"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "write_text_file", "description": "Write text to a path under work_dir (creates parent dirs).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"relative_path": {"description": "Path under the workspace (not absolute).", "title": "Relative Path", "type": "string"}, "content": {"description": "Full fi